parameters: Ah... uh... It's so bright... Is it morning...?\n< ??? >
Oh my, you're awake. That's very good timing.\n< Male >

Ah, I am... yes, a broker. I work connecting
people with people.\n< Male >

Let's see... do you remember? You were found
collapsed outside the town.\n< Male >

Outside the town...? Why would I be in such a
place...?\n< ??? >

Well, that's what I'd like to know. But... I have
a hunch.\n< Broker >

You see, an unidentified black slime appeared in
the town of Castulum.\n< Broker >

Taking advantage of the chaos, monsters invaded
the town all at once.\n< Broker >

It was quite a gruesome scene. Men were killed,
and women were taken to their dens. In one night,
the town of Castulum became a ruin.\n< Broker >

I had heard it was a terrible town to begin with,
but who would have thought it would come to
this... Well... perhaps it was their own doing.\n< Broker >
You must have fled from that town, right?\n< Broker >

Ah, this must be such a shock that you've lost
your memory. Well, for me, that's more
convenient... *cough*\n< Broker >

Now then, your name. Can you at least tell me your
name?\n< Broker >

My name... My name is... ugh... sorry... I can't
remember.\n< ??? >

Hmm... I see. By the way, while you were sleeping,
there was a word you kept mumbling.\n< Broker >

Hmm. Then let's do this. It's troublesome not to
have a name, so for the time being, let's say your
name is Splendour.\n< Broker >
Ah, it's a very... nice name...\n< Splendour >

Then, Ms. Splendour, you are to meet a certain
person from now on.\n< Broker >

Just meeting is fine. The rest will be led by the
other party.\n< Broker >

Oh, and are you thirsty? I've prepared some tea
here for you to enjoy before meeting them.\n< Broker >
(This tea has a strong bitterness to it...)\n< Splendour >

Now then, I'll go prepare some things, so please
wait here for a while.\n< Broker >

My vision is still blurry. I want to wash my
face... Where is the washroom...?\n< Splendour >

Is this the washroom? It's a bit shabby, but I
should be able to wash my face here.\n< Splendour >
My reflection is in the mirror.\n< Splendour >

What's this... growing out of my head... Horns?
Like a unicorn's...\n< Splendour >
Ahh... ahhhh... I remember now...\n< Serena >
I am... I am my own radiance...\n< Serena >

With these hands, I take life... and then... I
devour it...\n< Serena >

I see... this monstrous form mixed within me...
it's a curse from you, isn't it...\n< Serena >

This form... it's just like the old me... Did you
change my body so I wouldn't forget...\n< Serena >

You won't allow me to die... You're saying I must
live on eternally with the form of one who bears
sin...\n< Serena >
I hear something... Is there someone there?\n< Serena >

It's sealed with some kind of ice magic. Perhaps a
spell is needed...\n< Serena >

With my current power, I surely won't be able to
open it... I'm sorry...\n< Serena >

With my current power, I surely won't be able to
open it... I'm sorry...\n< Serena >
There must be a hint somewhere...\n< Serena >
If I walk around, I might find something...\n< Serena >
It seems we only have one chance to thaw.\n< Serena >
Are the preparations... good enough?\n< Serena >
It seems I made a mistake...\n< Serena >
Cough... Cough... My throat is in bad shape...\n< Serena >
Ah-, ah-... It's a bit hard to talk...\n< Serena >
Mr. Splendour, please come as you are ready.\n< Broker >

Phew! What kind of place is this to be locked up
in!\n< ??? >

Uh...huh? Have we met before...perhaps...a long
time ago?\n< ??? >

Ah, but the hair color is different, so maybe I'm
mistaken.\n< ??? >

What's wrong? Are you feeling ill? Your complexion
is terrible. Did something...happen?\n< ??? >
...I have committed a sin...a very grave sin...\n< Serena >

I...left my home...the place of my birth, brought
shame upon my family...and took something precious
with my own hands...\n< Serena >
Such as I am...is it even right for me to live...\n< Serena >

Perhaps it was a mistake for me to have been born
at all...\n< Serena >

I'm sure the people who gave birth to you did so
with love.\n< ??? >

Children...babies take many days to grow and
develop slowly.\n< ??? >

There can be misfortunes along the way that lead
to loss.\n< ??? >

Sometimes people give up due to environmental
factors or health issues.\n< ??? >

There may have been many hardships. But your
parents...\n< ??? >
So...the words that are fitting for you are...\n< ??? >

Besides, there must have been many people who
eagerly awaited your birth.\n< ??? >

Well...I can't say there weren't any twisted
parts!\n< ??? >

Hehe...that's true...who knows how many trials God
will give...\n< Serena >

And as for sin? It's not that dying is
unforgivable, but perhaps it's because God wants
you to live that you were allowed to survive.\n< ??? >
I am grateful. I am fine now.\n< Serena >
It was truly good to have met you.\n< Serena >
Ah, at least tell me your name------\n< Serena >

Now then, that man! I'll be returning the favor
from earlier!\n< ??? >

Hehehe...that's true. Perhaps we don't need names
after all.\n< Serena >
Now, let's go. Let us do what must be done.\n< Serena >

Why do I feel this way... It feels nostalgic...
Different from Splend-r... Something else...\n< Serena >

Could this be, memory... thawing... method. Six
letters... a person's, name perhaps...?\n< Serena >

Now that I think about it, this red hair... It
resembles the doll I found before... Maybe the
name of that doll is...\n< Serena >

My face is vaguely reflected on the surface of the
water...\n< Serena >
The face of a sinner who has devoured a friend...\n< Serena >
